comments.raw_text:
In pseudo-code:

let A = list of all addons;

if (A.size < some_cutoff(1)) {
  A.each(draw_item);
} else {
  let P = A.where(is_pinned);
  let FA = (A - P).sort(by_access_freceny, larger_to_smaller).limit(some_cutoff(2));

  FA.remove_all(function(x) x.frecency == 0);

  let RI = (A - P - FA).sort(by_install_or_upgrade_date, Present_to_Past).limit(some_cutoff(3));

  if (P.size > 0) {
    draw_group_header("Pinned");
    P.each(draw_item);
  }

  if (FA.size > 0) {
    draw_group_header("Frequently accessed");
    FA.sort(by_name, A_to_Z).each(draw_item);
  }

  draw_group_header("Recently installed");
  RI.each(draw_item);
}



In English:

show the mockup if it's below some cut-off.

Otherwise, draw 3 groups (bounded in size by cut-offs):

A pinned list

A frecency list sorted by name (A to Z)

A recently installed (or upgraded) list sorted by date (present to past)


1. An addon should appear only once
2. "access frecency" refers to accessing the "options" of the addon.
3. Needs the ability to pin an addon somewhere. Possibly in addons manager.

